      "type": "tool-result",
      "delayMs": 1400,
      "toolCallId": "e6",
      "output": "# /jobshomepage\n\n**Headline:** \"We'd love to help you find your ideal flexible job.\"\n\n⚠️ **No job vacancies are displayed on this page.**\nThe site says: \"Here you can find details of all the job vacancies we\ncurrently have available\" — but the actual list is gated behind a\nZoho Recruit registration flow. Visitors can't browse current roles.\n\nNo filters. No search. No categories. No salary information.",
      "isError": false,
      "isCollapsed": false
    },
    {
      "id": "e8",
      "type": "thinking",
      "delayMs": 500,
      "durationMs": 2200,
      "label": "Identifying improvements"
    },
    {
      "id": "e9",
      "type": "assistant-message",
      "delayMs": 200,
      "content": "Now I understand the brand. It's a genuinely good consultancy with a strong, clear niche — but the website has three problems holding it back:\n\n**1. The jobs page is a dead end.** Visitors are told \"we have vacancies\" and then asked to register for a Zoho portal. There are no browsable roles. This is the single biggest issue — recruitment sites live or die on job visibility.\n\n**2. The IA is fragmented across 25+ pages.** /ourethos, /our-story, /our-awards, /meet-the-team, /why-choose-us, /how-we-work, /ourservices… all of these belong together. The sitemap is confusing both for users and for SEO.\n\n**3. The value proposition is buried.** \"THE RECRUITMENT CONSULTANCY for Part-Time, Hybrid and Fractional roles\" works as a tagline, but the homepage doesn't answer \"what does flexible actually mean, who have you placed, and how do I find a job today?\"\n\nHere's my plan for the rebuild:\n\n- **Hero:** sharper headline (\"Work that fits your life\") with dual CTAs — browse jobs / hiring?\n- **Live job listings on the homepage** — this is the critical fix. Real cards with salary, hours, location, tags for Part-time / Hybrid / Fractional / 4-day / Remote\n- **Inline search** with working-pattern filters (not just a keyword box)\n- **Social proof up front** — 3 testimonials, numbers (placements, retention, avg salary)\n- **Dedicated \"For employers\" section** with a stats card and a clear brief CTA\n- **Founder section** bringing Helen's story forward — it's a genuine differentiator\n- **Consolidated footer** — the 25-page IA collapses into Candidates / Employers / Company groups\n- **Newsletter subscribe** — Monday roles digest (owns the recurring touchpoint)\n\nBuilding it now as a single self-contained `index.html`.",
      "streamingSpeed": "normal"
    },
